{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_brookland_ver01/data/sn84026749/00205696404/1930112601/0120.xml":{"full_text":"b*\nEDITORIAL PAGE J\n<t OF THE\nHearst Papers Advocate\n1. \"Honest friendship with all nations, entangling alliances\n4 with none.\"\u2014George Washington.\n~i. Proportional representation in the United States Senate, no\nState to have less than two Senators. Legislation to enforce\nprompt constitutional reapportionment in the House of\nRepresentatives.\n3. Separate departments of the Army, of the Navy, and of the\nAir Forces, all united under a Secretary of National Defense.\nd. Federal action to the limit of Federal powers to abolish\nilliteracy under a Secretary of Education.\nx 5. Installation of the President on the first of January follow-\ning the November election.\nt. Selective immigration to admit only those suited for Ameri\ncan citizenship and American needs.\n7. Deportation of undesirable aliens and extension of citizen\nship period to 10 years.\n8. Complete publicity for income taxes to prevent big tax\ndodgers from escaping taxation.\nModification of the Volstead act to permit light wines and\nbeers under Federal regulation.\nBeginning of \u201cRacketeering\u201d\nIn District of Columbia\nTests of Police Efficiency Are in Sight.\nThere may be nothing alarming in reports of minor at*\ntempts at \u201cracketeering\u201d and strong arm underworld tactics\ntn this city, but it behooves the police not to be overly\nsanguine in these matters.\nIt is but a matter of time when the \u201cracketeering\u201d game\nwill be attempted here and when, if the police do not cope\npromptly with it, the easy-money schemes of the criminal\nunderworld will get a footing.\nThe menace to this city is not in individual attempts of\nloafing criminals to copy the ways of organised crime. It is\nin racketeering getting a foothold, under the direction of\naspiring criminals of the Al Capone type.\nIt is in this menace that our Police Department should be\nprepared for rapid, efficient action and the prosecuting offi\ncials of our courts ready to put offenders on trial without de\nlay. making examples of originators of this foul game.\nThe action of law enforcing agencies must be short and\nsharp that Washington may not be afflicted with modern\ncriminals ready for any crime.\nThis \u201cprotection\u201d game will naturally make its appearance\napjong owners of small establishments, most of them foreigners\nwho fear that they will not have efficient police protection.\nIf successful in these kinds of places it spreads to larger\nbusiness establishments.\nWhether existing laws are ample to punish racketeers is for\nthe police and District Attorney to determine. If there is\nany shortcoming in our laws then Congress should be asked to\npass necessary laws, containing teeth.\nX.-\nSenator Capper has a good law before the Senate. It was\nrequested by high police officials. It defines vagrancy and\nfixes\nwith criminal records who have no visible means of honest and\nreputable livelihoods.\nThe police would be able to hold vagrants longer than at\npresent and have time to investigate their histories.\nThe bill should be passed by Congress at THIS SESSION.\nDay of Real Thankfulness\nIn tomorrow\u2019s observance of Thanksgiving Day Washing\nton people have every reason to be genuinely thankful.\nThere is distress and need here, but it does not reach the\nproportions of other cities. It will be cared for in generous\nmanner, too, if the cases are known.\nThere is less unemployment here than in other cities of\nsimilar size and public and private agencies are struggling\nhard to better conditions. They are succeeding.\nThose who have work are better off than a year ago, be\ncause prices are lower and their money goes further.\nWe should be grateful that our conditions are such that\nwe are going to be able to help the unfortunate, filling our\nhearts with joy and content. Let that purpose be our aim\nuntil conditions return to normal.\nRoadside Stands in Bay State\nWhen the Maryland legislature meets it will undoubtedly\nconsider measures to improve the numerous roadside stands of\nall kinds, many of them most unsightly and menaces to health.\nIn 1932, with the George Washington celebration centering\nin this city, Americans by thousands will use Maryland roads\nto and from Washington and for sight seeing. It would be\npleating to them to see Maryland under inviting circum\nstances.\nThe Department of Agriculture of Massachusetts is adopting\nkn interesting policy for roadside stands in that State selling\nlocal products of good quality, including vegetables and fruits\ngrown near the stands. Neat and attractive stands will be\nallowed to display State insignia on their signs and will sub\nmit to official inspections.\n.I\nThe Marry-Go-Round\nBy Helen Rowland-\nThe Sweet and Low-Down\nWedding-rings are very much\nwider this season\u2014wider and\nfewer. In fact, they are be\ncoming so rare that a woman\nwants one big enough to\nSHOW.\nA woman has reached the\nage of discretion when she be\ngins to believe the worst that\nher looking-glass tells her. and\ngives up her lipstick; a man,\nwhen he believes the worst\nthat his doctor tells him, and\ngives up whoopee parties.\n\nSome husbands are almost as\nhard to bear with when they\nare trying to be \u201cgood and\nnoble\u201d as when they are peev\nish and natural.\nAt 16, every girl believes\nsecretly that she was \u201cjust made\nfor love.\u201d Later she discovers,\nto her chagrin, that she was\njust made for stenography,\nmanicuring**or darning socks\nThe average man\u2019s respect\nfor woman\u2019s intelligence is\nmanifested in the fact that,\neven in this enlightened day,\nwomen\u2019s hats are priced. |458;\nwhereas, a five-dollar hat in a\nman\u2019s shop costs exactly five\ndollars\u2014and no fooling!\nDrinks used to be diluted\nwith romance and sentiment,\nin the good old days. But now\nwe take them both \u201cstraight,\u201d\nand wonder why they leave us\nwith such a headache.\nAn ideal wife, according to a\nman\u2019s notion, is a comforting,\nunderstanding woman, to whom\nhe can turn for solace or pro\ntection, when \u201cthe other wom\nan\u201d is beginning to \u201cget on his\nnerves.\u201d\nAnd old-fashioned girl is one\nwho hursts into tears instead\nof into profanity when her\nshoulder-strap breaks, her car\nbalks, or a man makes her\nfurious.\nmtim\nWASHINGTON...TIMES\nRunning for Cover By t. e. Powers\ny/AU- st. Bears yip-ZincT Fast\n/All soviet Qoods\nr y CO/'IE OUT. yot/j FAC ins BAM DontFo\u00df-\nIKEEP) t JL\nour) ,FFWy=R Mi\nSoviet\n(a -ZZ\u2014 -7, 7///7////W''\nI {/CdAie J J r\" rzfc- .Y/'f/...,.\n(1\nCA PONE\nLetters to the Editor From Readers of The Times\nFriend of Unemployed\nGives His Views\nEditor Times:\nAs a friend of the unem\nployed and of labor in\nI have given considerable\nthought to the deplorable con\ndition of affairs at present con\nfronting our country. While\nPresident Hoover and his able\ncommission will no doubt give\na good account of themselves\nand are to be commended for\ntheir efforts in ameliorating\nthe situation, there is one\nremedy that has occurred to me,\nwh|ch if put in effect will do\nmuch toward helping the good\nwork along.\nXt i\u00bb this! Instead of having\nmarried women on their pay\nrolls, let the stores, banks, of\nfices, and, factories throughout\nthe nation, dispense with their\nservices and employ others in\ntheir places. The married wom\nan\u2019s sphere is pre-eminently the\nhome, and let her shine in it,\na comfort and a blessing to her\nhusband and children, who es\npecially in this age, need her\ntender ministrations and loving\ncounsel. In the District of\nColumbia there is a large per\ncentage of this class among the\nwage-earners, and they are tak\ning the bread out of many a\nhungry mouth by continuing in\nsuch employment,\u2014R. H. B. J.\nSelf-Government for\nYoung Students\nEditor Times:\nHenry James\u2019 book on the\nlate President Eliot, of Har\nvard should have intense in-\nWISE MEN\nThe virtue of parents is a\ngreat dowry. \u2014Horace.\nOur patience will achieve\nmore than our force.\n\u2014Burke.\nIf wisdom were, offered to\nme on condition thdt I should\nkeep it close and not commu\nnieate it, I should refuse the\ngift. \u2014Seneca.\nLawyers are always more\nready-to get a man into trou\nbles than out of them.\n\u2014Goldsmith.\nBeware of desperate steps.\nThe darkest day,\nLive till tomorrow, will have\npassed away. Cowper.\nLiberty is not in any form\nof government. It is in the\nheart of the free man; he car\nries it with him everywhere.\n\u2014Rousseau.\nThe more we study, the more\nwe discover our ignorance.\n\u2014Shelley\nIt is easy in l the world to\nlive' after the world\u2019s opinions;\nit is easy in solitude to live\nafter our own; but the Great\nMan is he who in the midst\nof the crowd keeps with perfect\nsweetness the Independence- ot\n>\u2014.?M>i.\nterest for the general reader,\nespecially for our public school\nteachers, but Mr. James fails\nto give Eliot adequate credit\nfor his grand broad views on\neducation for democracy.\nHe thinks of him too much\nas an expert on higher educa\ntion. Os course, Eliot was this\nbut a great deal more. He\nwas much more than a high\nbrow. Every child in the land\nwill get inspiration from him.\nEliot was president of the\nNational Education Association\nwhich exists \u201cto improve the\npublic schools,\u201d and the school\nListen, World!\nAre you saying that you\nhaven\u2019t any reason to be thank\nful today? You have always one\nreason for supreme thankful\nness. That reason is YOUR\nSELF.\nIf you can\u2019t be thankful for\nanything else, BE THANKFUL\nFOR YOURSELF.\nYes, I know, you may not be\nGod\u2019s greatest gift to humanity.\nBUT YOU\u2019RE GOD\u2019S GREAT\nEST GIFT TO YOURSELF.\nYou are your own best bet.\nYour own biggest opportunity.\nAnd you have, within you, the\npower to build heaven for your\nself. Or 57 varieties of hell.\nPerhaps you\u2019ve found life a\npretty futile affair this last\nyear. You wanted a chance.\nYou couldn\u2019t get it. You longed\nfor adventures. There weren\u2019t\nany. Everyone else had all the\nluck. What was the use of liv\ning.\nThe Wrong Place\nTrouble with you was\u2014YOU\nWERE LOOKING FOR LIFE\nIN THE WRONG PLACE. Life\nisn\u2019t to be found OUTSIDE you.\nIt is to be found INSIDE you.\nThere, Inside you, is your\nCHANCE and your LUCK.\nYOU\u2019RE A GOLD MINE, BUT\nYOU DON\u2019T KNOW IT!\nIF YOU\u2019LL BACK YOUR\nSELF, AS YOU WOULD ANY\nOTHER BUSINESS PROPOSI\nTION, NOTHING CAN STOP\nYOU.\nWhat do I mean by \u201cback\ning\" yourself? BELIEVING IN\nYOURSELF AND ACTING AS\nIF YOU BELIEVED. Stop be\ning sorry for yourself. Stop ap\nproaching life with a sneer and\nyourself with a sob. Stop sus-\nTIMES KNOWLEDGE TEST\nDo you know\n1. With what country do\nyou connect Guy Fawkes?\n2. Where is De Soto buried?\n3. Who convened Barebone\u2019s\nParliament in England?\n4. What was the unfinished\nnovel of Joseph Conrad?\n5. What is the cdlor of ala\nbaster?\nFill each blank\n6. The first president of the\nAmerican Red Cross Society\nwas\n1. The first president of the\ntMawi\u00dfepubfc waa\nteachers know how near this\nwas to his heart. He said:\n\u201cThere is only one way of\nteaching young men to gov\nern themselves, namely by\nletting them try.\u201d\nHe also said*.\n\u201cThe real object in educa\ntion. so far as the develop\nment of character is con\ncerned, is to cultivate in the\nchild a capacity for self\ncontrol or self-government,\nnot a habit of submission to\nan overwhelming, arbitrary,\nexternal power, but a habit\nof obeying the dictates of\ne pectins bad luck and advertis\ning failure. A sales line like\nthat would kill any commodity.\nAct as if you had something\nfine to offer! Bet on yourself!\nShow your faith in yourself.\nFaith\u2014that\u2019s the most power\nful force on earth. That\u2019s the\nthing we\u2019re all looking for in\nthe other fellow. We\u2019re all\ncowards at heart. We\u2019re all\nsecretly bewildered and dis\ncouraged. We want to BE\nSURE. And well follow the\nman who IS sure. A man like\nthat, even though he be only\na ditch digger by trade, is a\nsort of haven for all other men.\nAnd moreover, he\u2019s RELIABLE.\nFor the man who believes in\nhimself, will work for himself,\nand he\u2019ll stake all his pride on\nthe job. You can bank on a\nman who banks on himself.\nBe Thankful\nBELIEVE IN YOURSELF\nAND THE WORLD WILL BE\nLIEVE IN YOU.\nBE THANKFUL FOR YOUR\nSELF\u2014AND GRATEFUL BE\nCAUSE YOU HAVE BEEN\nGRANTED THE GREAT AD\nVENTURE OF BEING YOUR\nSELF.\nWhat if it has meant pain?\nBe glad you CAN suffer, that\nyou\u2019re sensitive enough to\nsuffer. What if you are broke?\nAs long as you have YOUR\nSELF, you can\u2019t be broke,\nAs long as you have your\nself and believe in yourself\nyou can begin life all over\nagain any minute you choose.\nBEGIN IT OVER AGAIN\nNOW!\n(Copyright, .by Kins Feature*\nSyndicate,\u2019 Inc.)\n8. Lady Mary intro-\nduced to western Europe the\npractice of inoculation for\nsmallpox.\n9. The spineless cactus is an\nachievement of\n10. The Panama Canal was\nbegun in 1861 and was com\npleted in\nMatch correctly\n11. comfort routine\n12. commence I desolate\n13. forlorn solace\n14. single begin\n15. timid sole\nMmw Mantine FmU\nhonor and duty, as enforced\nby active will-power within\nthe child.\n\u201cStudent self-government\nenforces positive activity; It\nappeals steadily to motives\nin the boys which will serve\nthem >\u00bbhen they become\nmen; and it is constantly\ntrying to develop in the boy\nish community the capacity\nof self-rovernment.\u201d\nVery truly yours,\nSOPHIE POLLACK,\nSecretary Self-Government\nCommittee, New York City.\nCommend* Btanl Favoring\nCounty Change of Govt.\nEditor Timet:\nAs a resident of Arlington\ncounty please accept my sin\ncere appreciation for your edi\ntorial of November 11 deal\ning with the change in form\nof government of (Arlington\ncounty.\nYour pointed references to\nmodem requirements of county\ngovernment and the type of\nexecutives to direct same\nshould not only be of great\ninterest to the thinking peo\nple of Arlington county but\nshould serve to still further\nenlighten them on the respon\nsibility of citizenship.\nJOHN ,A. PETTY.\nONCE-OVERS\nMoney Isn\u2019t Everything\nK You may feel that you can be\nlittle good in the world because\nyou have not much money.\nWhy is it that you associate\nhelpfulness and money when\nyou consider whether you\nmight not help some other per\nson?\nMoney is not needed so often\nas kinds words, friendy sugges\ntions and a genuine interest in\nthe welfare of the recipient.\nCertainly you are not too\npoor to offer this kind of help.\nSympathy with those who\nhave a x hard time to adjust\nthemselves to a load is one of\nthe finest things you can lend.\nCheery words and thoughtful\ndeeds when it comes to the ill\nand afflicted make an other\nwise unendurable day seem\nshorter.\nBut you don\u2019t like to make\npersonal effort and unselfish\nattention is not in your line, so\nyou prefer to gauge your use\nto the word from the financial\nend of the proposition.\nYou never aid others when it\nentails work or self-denial and\nyour friends are beginning to\nfind this out.\nThey don\u2019t want your money,\nthey want to find your heart on\nthe right side when they are*\nheavy laden, and if you have\nthe right spirit you will forget,\nyour own pleasure and five of\nymmalL\nWASHINGTON, D. C.,'\nNOVEMBER 26,1930\nHere\u2019s the Speed Champion\nQueer Looking, but It Goes.\nCAPT. FRANK HAWKS, CHAMPION AMERICAN AIR PILOT\nOF TODAY, IN HIS PLANE THAT BREAKS RECORDS.\nIn this machine Captain Frank Hawks, American champion\nspeed flier, goes over 200 miles per hour.\nIt is a queer looking vehicle, but it MAKES and BREAKS\nrecords, thanks to its engine, and, above all, thanks to the\nengine at work in the brain of Captain Hawks.\nWho would have thought, a few years ago, that a man\nwould actually fly in a machine like this from the Pacific to\nthe Atlantic Ocean in twelve hours?\nWho can tell what the high speed ships of the future will\nbe like?\nAnd, for that matter, who can tell what automobiles, also\ncapable of two hundred miles an hour already, will be like in\nyears to come, with special roads, and no speed limits?\nr\u2014r\n.M M pt w\nA NEW AUTOMOBILE TYPE.\nHere is a sample of the latest automobile, with more engine\nthan body. It is built in England where they make their auto*\nmobiles by hand, slowly, and can try all kinds of new things.\nThey have an excellent idea in this automobile, of great\npower and speed, and that is a ROOF OF GLASS, that will\nnot shatter, all the rest of the glass being of the same kind.\nThe ordinary closed car shuts in the driver and passengers\nand shuts OUT the beauty of sky and clouds.\nA man in a closed car traveling through beautiful country\nis like a man walking in a magnificent cathedral with his\numbrella up.\nIn this new type of car you look up through the glass roof\nat the clouds by day or the stars at night, and the sun can\nshine down on you.\nOur grandchildren will go in their automobiles from two to\nthree hundred miles an hour along roads unobstructed, with\nno speed limit, at least five hundred feet wide.\nIn the air they will go five hundred miles an hour and\nfaster.\nLet ns hope their errands will be worthy of their speed.\nChristmas Bonuses\nWhy Wait Until Christmas?\nMany firms will give Christmas bonuses to, employes this\nyear, as usual. In the aggregate, these sums will amount to\nhundreds of thousands of dollars.. Why not give them NOW,\nin ample time to be used for Christmas shopping, instead of\nwaiting until December 24th or 25th?\nEmployes would be fully as appreciative\u2014in fact, more\nso. And the money would be a distinct boom to business.\nEarly shopping is urged at every Christmas. It is a kind\nness to overworked clerks and salespeople, and is a help to-the\nPostoffice Departipent, which already is renewing its appeal\nto the public to mail Christmas parcels promptly.\nEarly shopping is difficult, however, for those without\nmoney to shop.\nThe bonuses would help many to solve this problem. Busi\nness houses can contribute to business revival by making them\navailable now, when they are most needed.\nA Giant of Science\nBy Archibald Henderson\nAmong the men, only eight\nin.number, pronounced by Ber\nnard Shaw to be makers of\nuniverses, stands the name of\nClaudius Ptolemy. Although\nthis figure emerges from the\nmists of antiquity as one of\nthe pre-eminent masters in as\ntronomical science, almost noth\ning is known either of his life\nor career. It is known that he\nwas a native of Alexandria,\nbut the year of his birth is\nunknown. He was certainly\nmaking astronomical observa\ntions as early as 127 A. D.;\nand he was in the full tide of\nhis fame about the-year 150.\nJust three centuries earlier, or\nabout 150 B. C\u201e flourished Hip\nparchus, upon whose work Ptol\nemy based his own remarkable\nsystem. It was a triumph of\nmathematical ingenuity; and\nthe skill with which this com\nplex system of epicycles and\neccentrics was worked out re\nmains a source of amazement,\neven rt the present day.\nThe Ptolemaic theory assumes\nthe immobility of the earth, the\nrevolution of the sun around\nthe earth, and the daily rota\ntion of the whole universe\nGround the earth as a center.\nIt was assumed that a planet\nmoved in a circle around an\nimaginary point, while this\nimaginary point described a\ncircle around the earth. Ptolemy\nim\u00bb\u00bbMta\u00df at and\nit is necessary to know what-an\nepicycle is. Suppose a motorist\npicks up a nail in the tire of\nhis automobile. The head of\nthe nail stuck in the tire\ntraverses or describes in space\na curve as the automobile\ntravels along. This curve de\nscribed by the nail-head is\ncalled an epicycle. If you\nimagine the automobile travel\ning around a huge circle, the\nhail-head describes the kind of\nepicycle used by Ptolemy in\nhis work.\nA simple mechanical con\ntrivance will give a good Idea\nof the sort of mathematical\nfigure Ptolemy used in his\nastronomical system. Imagine\ntwo arms fixed to one an\nother, each swinging freely.\nThe circular motion of the\nfirst arm carries the second\narm around with it; and all\nthe while, the second arm des\ncribes a circular motion on its\nown account. The figure de\nscribed in space by the end of\nthe second arm is called an\nepicycle or epicycloid. It is of\nthe same general form as the\napparent motions of the planets\nacross the heavens. In mod\nem times, the motion of the\nbodies in the solar system were\ncalculated from the sun taken\nas center, which greatly simpli\nfied the mathematical problems\ntented.","height":"30263","width":"24244"}}
